HEADWORD: Scolithus
<hw>Scol"i*thus</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>skw`lhx</grk> a worm + <grk>li`qos</grk> a stone.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A tubular structure found in Potsdam
sandstone, and believed to be the fossil burrow of a marine
worm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

